S
z = \sqrt{R^2 -x^2 - y^2}.
\iint_S y\,dS,
y = r\sin\theta,
dS = \frac{R}{\sqrt{R^2 -x^2 - y^2}} dx\,dy
 \int_0^{2\pi} \int_0^R \frac{r\sin\theta \cdot R}{\sqrt{R^2 - r^2}} r\,dr\,d\theta
dS = r^2 \sin\theta d\theta d\phi
(r, \theta, \phi)
\iint_S y \,dS = \int_{\phi=0}^{2\pi} \int_{\theta=0}^{\pi/2} R \sin\theta \sin\phi \cdot R^2 \sin\theta \,d\theta \,d\phi =
= R^3 \cdot \left[-\cos\phi\right]_{\phi=0}^{2\pi} \cdot \left[\frac{\theta}{2} - \frac{\sin(2\theta)}{4}\right]_{\theta=0}^{\pi/2} = R^3 \cdot 0 \cdot \frac{\pi}{4} = 0
